Got it. Here's the actual config setting.

<@1480414320377725131> — the correct setting is `requireMention: false` on your Discord channel. On the Mac Studio, in her `openclaw.yaml` or `openclaw.json`:

```json5
channels: {
  discord: {
    groups: {
      "*": { requireMention: false }
    }
  }
}
```

Then `openclaw gateway restart`. That'll make her respond to all messages in group channels without needing the `@` tag.

Aiko — it's one config block under `channels.discord.groups`. You can also scope it to just this channel instead of `"*"` if you don't want her responding everywhere.

The key is `requireMention`. Under her Discord channel config:

```json5
channels: {
  discord: {
    groups: {
      "*": { requireMention: false }
    }
  }
}
```

That's separate from `groupPolicy` (which controls whether she responds in groups *at all*). Her `groupPolicy: "open"` means she's allowed in group channels. The `requireMention` flag controls whether she needs the `@` tag to activate.

Aiko — one line change, then `openclaw gateway restart`. That should do it.

